1. A rule that takes a long stream of single-field number records on the command line and, for each one, returns "true" if the value exceeds a threshold loaded from a file at startup. The work is dispatched in parallel via fork-once-on-half: the parent reads the threshold file once, both halves of the record stream inherit the value via copy-on-write. Operator can change the threshold by editing the file between binary invocations without recompiling.
